  "content": "## Task 11: Wire RAG Pipeline into CLI Server Startup\n\n## Task 12: Full Pipeline Integration Test\n\nAn end-to-end test that exercises retrieve → augment → trace capture.\n\n**Files:**\n- Create or modify: `crates/tests/integration/rag_e2e_test.rs` (or add to existing e2e)\n\n**Step 1: Write the integration test**\n\n```rust\n#[tokio::test]\nasync fn test_rag_pipeline_e2e() {\n    // Setup: LiteStore + MockEngine + VectorRetriever + StructuredAugmenter\n    let dir = tempfile::tempdir().unwrap();\n    let config = corvia_common::config::CorviaConfig::default();\n\n    let store = Arc::new(corvia_kernel::lite_store::LiteStore::open(dir.path(), 3).unwrap())\n        as Arc<dyn corvia_kernel::traits::QueryableStore>;\n    store.init_schema().await.unwrap();\n\n    // MockEngine for deterministic embedding\n    let engine = Arc::new(MockEngine) as Arc<dyn corvia_kernel::traits::InferenceEngine>;\n\n    // Insert test knowledge\n    let mut idx = 0_usize;\n    let mut next_emb = || { idx += 1; vec![1.0, idx as f32 * 0.001, 0.0] };\n\n    for i in 0..10 {\n        let mut e = corvia_common::types::KnowledgeEntry::new(\n            format!(\"Knowledge about topic {i}\"), \"test-scope\".into(), \"v1\".into(),\n        ).with_embedding(next_emb());\n        e.entry_status = corvia_common::agent_types::EntryStatus::Merged;",
